{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/96357", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/96357/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/96357/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/96357/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/96357", "id": 1213537078, "node_id": "I_kwDOAAsO6M5IVRs2", "number": 96357, "title": "Rustc does not know that two structs have the same size, while it should.", "user": {"login": "wdanilo", "id": 1623053, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2MjMwNTM=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1623053?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/wdanilo", "html_url": "https://github.com/wdanilo", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/wdanilo/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/wdanilo/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/wdanilo/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/wdanilo/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/wdanilo/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/wdanilo/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/wdanilo/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/wdanilo/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/wdanilo/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [{"id": 630652267, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2MzA2NTIyNjc=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-feature-request", "name": "C-feature-request", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: A feature request, i.e: not implemented / a PR."}, {"id": 1944310735, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxOTQ0MzEwNzM1", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-layout", "name": "A-layout", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: Memory layout of types"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2022-04-24T05:13:54Z", "updated_at": "2022-04-25T07:27:23Z", "closed_at": "2022-04-25T07:27:22Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Hi, let's consider this code:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#[repr(transparent)]\r\npub struct UnitData<V, R> {\r\n    repr:    R,\r\n    variant: PhantomData<V>,\r\n}\r\n\r\ntrait TransmuteRanges {\r\n    type Out;\r\n    fn t1(self) -> Self::Out;\r\n}\r\n\r\nimpl<V, R> TransmuteRanges for std::ops::Range<UnitData<V, R>> {\r\n    type Out = std::ops::Range<R>;\r\n    fn t1(self) -> Self::Out {\r\n        unsafe { std::mem::transmute(self) }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt does not compile:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    |\r\n121 |         unsafe { std::mem::transmute(self) }\r\n    |                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n    |\r\n    = note: source type: `std::ops::Range<UnitData<V, R>>` (size can vary because of R)\r\n    = note: target type: `std::ops::Range<R>` (size can vary because of R)\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut this one compiles fine:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nimpl<V> TransmuteRanges for std::ops::Range<UnitData<V, usize>> {\r\n    type InnerType = usize;\r\n    fn t1(self) -> std::ops::Range<Self::InnerType> {\r\n        unsafe { std::mem::transmute(self) }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis one compiles fine too:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nimpl<V, R> TransmuteRanges for std::ops::Range<UnitData<V, R>> {\r\n    type Out = std::ops::Range<R>;\r\n    fn t1(self) -> Self::Out {\r\n        self.start.repr..self.end.repr\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI believe the transmute one should compile. Rustc version: rustc 1.62.0-nightly (8f36334ca 2022-04-06).", "closed_by": {"login": "oli-obk", "id": 332036, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzMjAzNg==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/332036?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/oli-obk", "ht